    <note>Hong(1) Hao [10156] Funerary declaration for wife, born Shen, who died in 1138 at age 50, in Hong Kuo, WJ, 77.1a-4a. Her elder brother, Shen(2) Songnian [13939], arranged for the marriage after learning that Hao had established himself by earning the jinshi. Sent on an embassy to Jin, he was forced to remain for 15 years before he was allowed to return to Song. Opposed Qin(1) Gui [8008] and dismissed first to prefect of Raozhou and then cashiered and exiled to Nanxiong zhou. He has many titles. One of his daughters married a Dong(1) Gongheng (no doubt from the distingished Raozhou Dong) and then remarried Yu(6) Zhiqing after Gongheng died. Neither husband in dataset. Jiangxi TZ, 21.38a; CBD, 2, 1505-1506.</note>
